I love my country, and it hurts not to be able to see my country, as I did for so many years. I hope that I will one day be able to live in a peaceful Colombia.

Fernando Botero

node.text:
During lockdown and on my daily exercise allowance I have decided to ditch all the technical lighting and document humanity while walking with my partner.

It is hard to contemplate what is happening in the world at the moment, as long as we have our loved ones close that's all that matters.

 - I felt the need to make a post on this page about bloating and what is commonly known as being morning skinny etc, firstly I want to make it totally clear that bloating is totally normal and every single person in the world experiences it - the first photo is me in the morning having just woken up and the second is me just before going to bed at the end of the day - in modern society people often become obsessed with this idea that bloated isn’t an “attractive look” or that it isn’t normal when in actual fact it is. It is human and is our bodies way of remaining healthy and digesting food etc without bloating we wouldn’t be human nor healthy - 
Fitness and health isn’t about the way you look it’s about feeling healthy and happy and being proud of you and your body and loving yourself - it took me a long time to be truly happy with myself and my body shape but I can say I love me and my body now whether I look like the first photo or the second. I know that I do fitness for myself and to make myself happy - everyone is on a journey and a road that leads you different ways and at the end of the day we are all human and I cannot express it enough that BLOATING IS NORMAL AND YOU SHOULD LOVE YOURSELF AND YOUR BODY üòö 
Everyone is perfect in their own way and that’s what makes everyone unique and you who you are üòä 
Hope you guys all had a lovely Saturday - please feel free to DM me if you wanna chat or have any questions :)) xxx

.
the past few months has been a roller coaster of emotions, more negative than positive. the constant anguish over the uncertain future and the jarring fact that i’ll be graduating during the worst recession in a century. although, home is  somewhere my heart lies but i don’t really enjoy being home as such. i always end up in stupid arguments, it makes me so frustrated and i don’t know where to take it out. however, i learned to focus my energy to heal instead of fueling my complex,,,
today, i look at things too carefully and i've been thinking about how everything around the corner has their hands tied to a moment that plays around them over and over again. i'm aware of the parts of myself which i’ve always neglected, and they mostly include the love i’ve for certain people in my life,,,, the world still moves like a blur but i forgive myself faster than it can revolve.
.
.
.
